Governors of the six South West states of Ekiti, Lagos, Ogun, Ondo, Osun and Oyo have resolved to enforce the use of face masks for anyone coming out of their homes from Friday, April 24, 2020 in the respective states. In a statement signed yesterday by the Ondo State Governor and Chairman of the South West Governors’ Forum, Arakunrin Oluwarotimi Odunayo Akeredolu where the governors dissolved the board of directors of O’dua Investment Limited, they also said entry points to the six states would be closed forthwith to contain the spread of COVID-19. They also resolved that people involved in essential services or dealing in medicine, water and consumable items, traders and market men/women should endeavour to wear nose masks while plying their trades. Amotekun has come to stay – Akeredolu Makarfi''s PDP faction meets in Ekiti, as Fayose demands refund of N10m donation towards Obj''s library Face masks now mandatory in Ogun, as lockdown takes toll